Our CANivore is indicating that CAN streaming is disabled. We currently can’t see the CANivore or any device attached to it in Phoenix Tuner either.

So far we’ve tried, 2 different CANivores, 2 different CAN loops, pulled the devices off the loop one by one and determined it’s not device specific. We’re also sure that everything is updated–a week ago when it was working we updated the firmware of all the devices on the bus.

Our bus uses a bus topology: containing 8 Falcons and 1 Pigeon 2.0.

Not sure if it’s code related but we’re on WPILib 2023.4.2 and the most up to date version of Phoenix lib. Here’s code as well.

This sounds similar to the behavior when our CANivore USB kernel module is not installed. Since the kernel module is installed as part of the roboRIO image, can you double check that your roboRIO is imaged with the latest version? (I think the latest is 2023_v3.1)
